thread.title: Pa. boys and girls: Hoeys lead Downingtown West to Eastern States crown
thread.title_full: Pa. boys and girls: Hoeys lead Downingtown West to Eastern States crown

title: Pa. boys and girls: Hoeys lead Downingtown West to Eastern States crown
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports Teammates Hannah Molloy, Mary Webb, Rachel Estey, Meri Twomey, and Maddie Sauer finished 16th, 23d, 38th, 40th, and 41st, respectively.
William Tennent Invitational. Rock Fortna led the field with a time of 15:44 to help Central Bucks West to a first-place finish at the 3.1-mile run. Teammates Brian Iatarola, Ben Smullen, and Joe Maguire came in fourth, sixth, and seventh, respectively. 
Sarah Smith finished fifth to lead Upper Dublin to a first-place finish. She completed the 3.1-mile run in a time of 19:31. 
Gettysburg XC Invitational. Maddie Villalba finished second and Central Bucks West won the invitational. She covered the 3.1-mile course in 18:51. Girls' Soccer Lauren Ruth and Sarah Welsh each scored, and Archbishop Wood won at Council Rock North, 2-0, in a nonleague match. Paige McQuillen made five saves.
In other nonleague action: 
Madison Dutton stopped 12 shots, and Christian Academy defeated host Phil-Mont Christian, 2-1. Grace Cryan and Grace Gormley netted goals. 
Maura Holst scored four times and host Radnor defeated Octorara, 5-1. Julianne Puckett added the fifth goal. Boys' Soccer Rodrigo Martinez and Logan Schwartz scored to lead Conestoga to a 2-0 Central League win at Lower Merion and remain unbeaten. Conestoga is ranked fourth in Southeastern Pennsylvania by The Inquirer.
Elsewhere in Central League play, Scott Campbell, Harrison Hotham, and Nate Perrins scored, and host Strath Haven defeated Springfield (Delco), 3-0. Perrins and Campbell each had an assist. 
Ches-Mont League. Jake Marcozzi's hat trick led West Chester East to a 3-1 victory at Avon Grove. Matt Grenell stopped 12 shots. 
Peter Ferraro scored the winner on a breakaway with six minutes remaining, and Unionville defeated visiting Downingtown West, 2-1. Alex Ilgner added a goal and an assist. Field Hockey Lily Fenstamacher and Brianna Mathis scored to lead Interboro to a 2-1 Del-Val League victory at Academy Park. Interboro clinched the Del-Val League title with the win.
